input_str: Kōnosuke Matsushita (松下 幸之助, Matsushita Kōnosuke, 27 November 1894 – 27 April 1989) was a Japanese industrialist who founded Panasonic, the largest Japanese consumer electronics company. To many Japanese, he is known as "the god of management".[citation needed] A biography of Matsushita's life called Matsushita Leadership was written by American business management specialist John Kot
